   546	
   547	The `systemPromptOptions` field gives extensions access to the same structured data Pi uses to build the system prompt. This lets you inspect what Pi has loaded — custom prompts, guidelines, tool snippets, context files, skills — without re-discovering resources or re-parsing flags. Use it when your extension needs to make deep, informed changes to the system prompt while respecting user-provided configuration.
   548	
   549	Inside `before_agent_start`, `event.systemPrompt` and `ctx.getSystemPrompt()` both reflect the chained system prompt as of the current handler. Later `before_agent_start` handlers can still modify it again.
   550	
   551	#### agent_start / agent_end / agent_settled
   552	
   553	`agent_start` fires when a low-level agent run begins. `agent_end` fires when that run ends, but Pi may still auto-retry, auto-compact and retry, or continue with queued follow-up messages. Use `agent_settled` for status integrations that need to know Pi will not continue running automatically.
   554	
   555	```typescript
   556	pi.on("agent_start", async (_event, ctx) => {});
   557	
   558	pi.on("agent_end", async (event, ctx) => {
   559	  // event.messages - messages from this low-level run
   560	});
   561	
   562	pi.on("agent_settled", async (_event, ctx) => {
   563	  // ctx.isIdle() is true here unless another extension started a new run.
   564	});
   565	```
   566	
   567	#### turn_start / turn_end
   568	
   569	Fired for each turn (one LLM response + tool calls).
   570	
   571	```typescript
   572	pi.on("turn_start", async (event, ctx) => {
   573	  // event.turnIndex, event.timestamp
   574	});
   575	
   576	pi.on("turn_end", async (event, ctx) => {
   577	  // event.turnIndex, event.message, event.toolResults
   578	});
   579	```
   580	
   581	#### message_start / message_update / message_end
   582	
   583	Fired for message lifecycle updates.
   584	
   585	- `message_start` and `message_end` fire for user, assistant, and toolResult messages.
   586	- `message_update` fires for assistant streaming updates.
   587	- `message_end` handlers can return `{ message }` to replace the finalized message. The replacement must keep the same `role`.
   588	
   589	```typescript
   590	pi.on("message_start", async (event, ctx) => {
   591	  // event.message
   592	});
   593	
   594	pi.on("message_update", async (event, ctx) => {
   595	  // event.message
   596	  // event.assistantMessageEvent (token-by-token stream event)
   597	});
   598	
   599	pi.on("message_end", async (event, ctx) => {
   600	  if (event.message.role !== "assistant") return;
   601	
   602	  return {
   603	    message: {
   604	      ...event.message,
   605	      usage: {
   606	        ...event.message.usage,
   607	        cost: {
   608	          ...event.message.usage.cost,
   609	          total: 0.123,
   610	        },
   611	      },
   612	    },
   613	  };
   614	});
   615	```
   740	Use this to update extension UI when `pi.setThinkingLevel()`, model changes, or built-in thinking-level controls change the active thinking level.
   741	
   742	### Tool Events
   743	
   744	#### tool_call
   745	
   746	Fired after `tool_execution_start`, before the tool executes. **Can block.** Use `isToolCallEventType` to narrow and get typed inputs.
   747	
   748	Before `tool_call` runs, pi waits for previously emitted Agent events to finish draining through `AgentSession`. This means `ctx.sessionManager` is up to date through the current assistant tool-calling message.
   749	
   750	In the default parallel tool execution mode, sibling tool calls from the same assistant message are preflighted sequentially, then executed concurrently. `tool_call` is not guaranteed to see sibling tool results from that same assistant message in `ctx.sessionManager`.
   751	
   752	`event.input` is mutable. Mutate it in place to patch tool arguments before execution.
   753	
   754	Behavior guarantees:
   755	- Mutations to `event.input` affect the actual tool execution
   756	- Later `tool_call` handlers see mutations made by earlier handlers
   757	- No re-validation is performed after your mutation
   758	- Return values from `tool_call` only control blocking via `{ block: true, reason?: string }`
   759	
   760	```typescript
   761	import { isToolCallEventType } from "@earendil-works/pi-coding-agent";
   762	
   763	pi.on("tool_call", async (event, ctx) => {
   764	  // event.toolName - "bash", "read", "write", "edit", etc.
   765	  // event.toolCallId
   766	  // event.input - tool parameters (mutable)
   767	
   768	  // Built-in tools: no type params needed
   769	  if (isToolCallEventType("bash", event)) {
   770	    // event.input is { command: string; timeout?: number }
   771	    event.input.command = `source ~/.profile\n${event.input.command}`;
   772	
